Prep Data

# devtools::install_github("derekmichaelwright/agData")
library(agData) # Loads: tidyverse, ggpubr, ggbeeswarm, ggrepel
library(plotly) # plot_ly()
# Prep data
dd <- read.csv("https://covid.ourworldindata.org/data/owid-covid-data.csv") %>%
  mutate(date = as.Date(date, format = "%Y-%m-%d"))
xx <- dd %>% filter(date == max(date)) %>% 
  select(location, total_deaths) %>% 
  arrange(desc(total_deaths))
DT::datatable(xx)

Cummulative

# Prep data
xx <- dd %>% 
  filter(location == "World") %>%
  select(location, date, Deaths=total_deaths, Cases=total_cases) %>%
  gather(Trait, Value, 3:4)
# Plot
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = date, y = Value / 100000, color = Trait)) +
  geom_line(size = 1) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("darkgreen","darkred")) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "months", date_minor_breaks = "months", date_labels = "%b") +
  theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
  labs(title = "Global COVID-19 Data (Cummulative)", 
       y = "Hundred Thousand", x = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Our World in Data")
ggsave("COVID_World_01.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)

Americas

# Prep data
areas <- c("Canada", "United States", "Mexico", "Brazil", "Argentina")
cols  <- c("darkred", "darkblue", "darkgreen", "darkorchid", "steelblue")
xx <- dd %>% 
  filter(location %in% areas) %>%
  mutate(location = factor(location, levels = areas))
# Plot
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = date, y = total_deaths_per_million, color = location)) + 
  geom_line(size = 1) + 
  theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
  scale_color_manual(values = cols) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "months", date_minor_breaks = "months", date_labels = "%b") +
  labs(title = "COVID-19 Deaths - Americas", 
       y = "Deaths Per Million", x = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Our World in Data")
ggsave("COVID_World_03.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)

Taiwan

# Prep data
cols  <- c("darkgreen", "darkred")
xx <- dd %>% filter(location == "Taiwan") %>%
  select(location, date, total_deaths, total_cases) %>%
  gather(Trait, Value, 3:4) %>%
  mutate(Trait = plyr::mapvalues(Trait, c("total_deaths", "total_cases"), c("Deaths", "Cases")))
# Plot
mp <- ggplot(xx, aes(x = date, y = Value, color = Trait)) + 
  geom_line(size = 1) + 
  theme_agData(legend.position = "bottom") +
  scale_color_manual(values = cols) +
  scale_x_date(date_breaks = "months", date_minor_breaks = "months", date_labels = "%b") +
  labs(title = "COVID-19 - Taiwan", 
       y = NULL, x = NULL,
       caption = "\xa9 www.dblogr.com/  |  Data: Our World in Data")
ggsave("COVID_World_07.png", mp, width = 6, height = 4)
